x4freetext: Both random and systematic errors were
taken into account. The possible major sources of
error were the uncertainty in the quantitative
isolation of tritium, the uncertainty in the relative
efficiency of the (beta-)-detector and the uncertainty
in the determination of neutron fluxes.
Combining all the individual errors the overall error
for each cross-section value was obtained.
